m Old English <i>sǣ</i> ‘sea’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’."]}]},{"name":"Philip","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Greek name <i>Philippos</i>, meaning ‘lover of horses’, from <i>philein</i> ‘to love’ + <i>hippos</i> ‘horse’. This was popular in the classical period and since. It was the name of the father of  Alexander the Great . It was also the name of one of Christ's apostles, of a deacon ordained by the apostles after the death of Christ, and of several other early saints.  See also  Philippa ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Philip Seton was born in 1135, his father, Saher de Seton II, was 48 and his mother, Janet De Giffard, was 47. He married Lady Matilda Corbet before 1185, in Europe. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1179, in Scotland, United Kingdom, at the age of 44."},"et":{"1135–1179":"1135–1179","1122–Female":"1122–Surnud","1165–Female":"1165–Surnud","1145–Female":"1145–Surnud","1185–Male":"1185–Surnud","1164–1211":"1164–1211","1087–1150":"1087–1150","1088–1165":"1088–1165","1135":"1135","1179":"1179","before 1135":"enne 1135","1211":"1211","1145":"1145","1122":"1122","1165":"1165","1088":"1088","1164":"1164","1087":"1087","1185":"1185","1150":"1150","Scotland":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Seton, East Lothian, Scotland":"Seton, Haddingtonshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1135–1179":"1135–1179","1122–Female":"1122–Kuollut","1165–Female":"1165–Kuollut","1145–Female":"1145–Kuollut","1185–Male":"1185–Kuollut","1164–1211":"1164–1211","1087–1150":"1087–1150","1088–1165":"1088–1165","1135":"1135","1179":"1179","before 1135":"ennen vuotta 1135","1211":"1211","1145":"1145","1122":"1122","1165":"1165","1088":"1088","1164":"1164","1087":"1087","1185":"1185","1150":"1150","Scotland":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Seton, East Lothian, Scotland":"Seton, Haddingtonshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1135–1179":"113